metadata.name: alchemy(maxima) #90
metadata.description:
This collection takes its main inspiration from the Turkish marbling art ‚ÄúEbru‚Äù and tries to spin it with a golden twist, hence alchemy :) 

alchemy(maxima) tries to create a composition either using one of the two grid types, and sometimes breaking them or in a totally chaotic way, but uses color harmony and rhythm to keep the chaos in check and the resulting image still somewhat interesting and sometimes golden-ish‚Ä¶

The name includes ‚Äúmaxima‚Äù because this is the first part of a 2-part series; its companion collection ‚Äúalchemy(minima)‚Äù will be released soon and as per my tradition will be freely available to maxima holders.

From the proceeds of the primary sales of alchemy(maxima),

- 33% will directly go to The Processing Foundation,
- 33% will fund the greater evil,
- 34% will be used to grow my collection.

So in a way, all the proceeds will go back into the ecosystem. This is my way of making up for taking tez out with my donations earlier.

If you are wondering what the hell ‚Äúthe greater evil‚Äù is, read about it here : 

https://twitter.com/evilnft/status/1544320804304961536?s=20&t=AoEfLfn32tGNR8JTi5Jjng

And find it here:

https://www.fxhash.xyz/u/the%20greater%20evil/collection

‚Äî

About the work: 

- 22 palettes - 7 new, 15 recycled,
- 3 main variants,
- 4 sub-variants each,
- 9 visible and some hidden features :)
- After going live, press ‚Äús‚Äù to save a png (at your screen resolution)
- No hi-res output due to the warp manipulating the pixel array directly, which means higher res equals to much higher computation time.

Thank you all in advance and have a good day!

Warp functions are based on this article by Inigo Quilez : https://iquilezles.org/articles/warp/

DISCLAIMER : I am not a good coder, I have tried to fix my past mistakes from my earlier projects to make some room for new mistakes :) I am learning on the way and certainly hoping that there aren't any huge bugs or anything, so you can enjoy your mint! Please hit me up if you have any concerns after minting and we can discuss a solution.

metadata.name: Returns #348
metadata.description:
Returns is an offline-first PWA and an interactive SVG. It combines the joy of interaction, digital color and minimalist sculpture with the potential of a long running, continuously unique visual. Based on ‚ÄúShipping‚Äù from 2016, it is inspired by Anne Truitt, Ugo Rondinone, Imi Knoebel, Kelly Ellsworth and many others.

A subdivision slices the viewport influenced by width, height and depth. Corners are cut by replacing them with two new points, pulled towards each other along the edges. Shapes are ‚Äúrounded" by repeating this step, keeping the new points close together. As colors change, so do the relations between shapes, even if geometry changes at a slower pace. New compositions are created on click or after a timeout. This progress over time allows for infinite iterations within the space of each token. It is the promise of a seeded starting point, plus the potential for unlimited new and unique iterations and states over time.

metadata.name: Smoke #88
metadata.description:
Inspired by the hot weather of the city.
Made in August 2022, Milano, Italy.

5 visible Features:
-Mood: tender, bleed, icecream, summer in Milano, evening, futurepunk, acid, love
-Size: small, regular, big
-Density: low, moderate, high, very high
-Speed: slow, moderate, fast
-Emissions: from 2 to 9

Some of the features are very rare, others less, some more common.

The design is being optimized to render at different speeds depending on the size of the window. The smaller the size, the faster the render and lower the detail, viceversa bigger the size, slower the render and higher the detail.
The moire effect of lines that are making the shades of the artwork will look thick with a low resolution, and become finer and more detailed the higher the resolution. You can use this feature to create quick previews or to save very Hi-Resolution images.
To save an image with the size of the window press S once the image is fully rendered.
The fx(hash) thumbnail is saved at 1425px x 1900px.
To save a Hi-Resolution image 3000px x 4000px press H and wait, the page will reload and start to render. Please be patient.

Built using p5js, published under CC-BY-NC-4.0 license.

Once the collection will be fully minted, the variations button will be disabled.

metadata.name: Part:Counterpart #211
metadata.description:
'Part:Counterpart' is an experiment in form, disintegration, and context. Each work is created within one of three modes, Part, Counterpart, or Part:Counterpart.

In experimenting, I've enjoyed taking a simple composition and breaking it down with various methods. This transforms the original composition into something new, but it also begins to lose what the original had to say. This isn't necessarily a bad thing, and I want to dive a little deeper and explore ideas as a sort of tangible substance. Already we're comparing ideas against their translations and evolutions, but what happens if we present them both within the context of the other?

Additionally, what if we present both of these ideas with echoes and tangents, discussion around the ideas and their practical applications instead of imagined? Sure, these aren't our idea, or even our translation, but they exist only because the originals do.

How does this change our opinion of the original? Is every idea destined to be picked apart and reimagined forever until it bears only a faint resemblance? Where is the line between our Counterpart and an echo?

This piece hopes to inspire contemplation on the nature of storytelling and artistic inspiration.

10% of ideas are encrypted to obscure the original Part.
Press ‚Äôs‚Äô to save a 3600x4500 png.
Press ‚Äòp‚Äô to save the original Part, pure and untouched.

metadata.name: Mental Lines #45
metadata.description:
To challenge a mind, the lines are arranged randomly and at different angles to show a mental creativity.
We usually draw these lines and drawings when we are anxious or bored. As a result, we often paint these shapes without full awareness, resulting in our mental preoccupations showing through.
Drawing with mixed lines, requires patience and perseverance. Additionally, mood swings are prone to be triggered by these images.
Convoluted lines are often drawn by people who are a little obsessive about their decisions and loved ones. In most cases, such pictures are drawn by introverted people.
Made by p5.js

press 's' to save original size

metadata.name: Celestial Rings: Algorithmic Study #95
metadata.description:
This is an exploration to create an abstract artwork using fields and growth rings and their interaction with each other. Each of the mints can have several central rings up to 14 and the rings interact with each other to form a larger structure. The structure of the rings can be uniform or rotating, with mixed colors or mono colors. Various color palettes and canvas sizes have been used.

Open it in live view and press ‚Äôs‚Äô to save image with high resolution.

Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Monsoon #110
metadata.description:
Optimization. It's something that haunts all programmers. Including me. But no longer! Monsoon is a study into the optimization of particle systems for the web. Looking especially deep into dynamic grids and dynamic frame rates.

As for the piece itself, it's a reference to how busy this modern world is. How we're all constantly on the go, whether that is physically, or mentally. Almost feeling like a monsoon. A storm of information. A storm of life. A storm of work. A storm of thoughts. A storm of emotions. A storm of everything. And it's all so fast.

As are the particles. They're all moving around these cyclones of information. Glowing up like neon signs in a busy city. Moving so fast it's almost a blur. Forming into something greater than the sum of its parts.

metadata.name: "Oneirism" #15
metadata.description:
Oneirism is a state of abnormal consciousness in which dream-like experiences and hallucinations happen while awake.
This describes the situation I went through learning and writing the algorithm for my first generative project (100 % code)
By learning p5js i discovered a new side of my artistic self and a path i want to follow to make art and express my feelings.
Thanks everyone from my bottom of my heart for helping and guiding me on those difficult last months.

--Features--

Palette : 16 different color schemes
Build : 2 Shapes
Step : "Low" "Medium" "High"
Rotation : 7 types (each type has more than 40 different outcomes)
Fading(Rare) : True or False

Press "s" to save a 1600x2000 PNG

Made with p5js.

Gtsiliakos_art, September 2022
